main event: A clerk-typist observed a dome-shaped, white UFO from her bedroom window in Washington, D.C. on 28 November 1956.
interesting points: The object was the size of a large beach umbrella and was observed for a total of 10 minutes., The observer first saw the object at about 25 degrees above the horizon in a westerly direction., The object moved northward and disappeared, then reappeared in the same position., There were no photographs included in the report., Weather conditions were calm and cloudless with good visibility at the time of the sighting.
location: Washington, D.C., United States of America
